Gary Vee on Gen-Z and the Lazy Girl/Guy trend. I’m fairly sure he is just speaking on knowledge workers, not menial workers/front line workers here. 

I think it’s actually a pretty complicated subject and any generalisation fails to give justice to edge cases. 

But I don’t think Lazy Work is the way to go for anyone who has the privilege to find work they find meaningful (of course not possible for all).

Interested to hear your thoughts in the comments!
